article.description: — Carlton Linguard had 21 points in UTSA's 93-60 victory over Arkansas-Fort Smith on Sunday.
article.headline: Linguard's 21 help UTSA defeat Arkansas-Fort Smith 93-60
article.linkText: Linguard's 21 help UTSA defeat Arkansas-Fort Smith 93-60
article.story: SAN ANTONIO -- — Carlton Linguard had 21 points in UTSA's 93-60 victory over Arkansas-Fort Smith on Sunday. Linguard added seven rebounds and Isaiah Wyatt had 20 points and five rebounds for the Roadrunners (5-4). Christian Tucker scored 17 points. Roland McCoy led the Lions in scoring, finishing with 13 points and two steals. Arkansas-Fort Smith also got 10 points from Jaden Monday. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
